value.0: This Duergar doesn't seem to be in a good mood.

Value.value: It's the hard-knock life, for us. Cotton blankets, 'steada wool. Empty bellies, 'steada full.
You brought me my lunch? Thanks!  *he pauses, then adds*  Since you're here, why don't you talk to Brocc, then Upaech over by the smelting pots?  I think they have errands which need to be done.

value.0: Also known as gray dwarves, the duergar are from the Underdark and are the evil cousins of the surface dwarves.

Value.value: I made this shield for a drow called Hanlur or Handur.. whatever. You can find him in the bar by the bazaar up in the city. He's easy to recognise: thin as a stick, effeminate, and perverted like the rest of his degenerated race. Make sure he pays the bill!
Before you head back up, though, go talk to Surt'hil Zau'tar. You can find him by crossing the bridge near the crane, and heading up to the tunnel entrance that leads to the Middledark.
He said the payment's on the way, eh? Good, good.  Here's a little payment for -you- then, for helping me out.  *hands over a sack of coins*
No time to chitchat, there's too much to be done around here!
Did you deliver the shield or what?

value.0: The drow are an evil subrace of elves, living deep underground in the dangerous Underdark.

Value.value: You seem a somewhat able ...person. My brother Argh'illes went to collect some spider eggs for breeding and didn't return. I suspect he may not have been careful enough. Go to the Spider Holes and find him. Give him this package with anti-venom.
Make sure you don't harm the spiders. You should take some invisibility potions with you to make sure you can move around undetected.  Don't forget to get some before heading into the tunnels!
Otherwise, the spiders will probably attack you - and we wouldn't want them coming to any harm, now would we?
You delivered the antidote? Excellent! Here, compensation for your work. *he hands over a large sack of coins*
Leave me to my duties, now.
What are you waiting for? My brother may be dying!

value.0: Svirfneblin or deep gnomes are reclusive, suspicious and resentful of intrusion.

Value.value: Pucor the miner is dealing with some very hard rocks in the mines. Bring him a new pick, the current one will probably be used up by now.
He shouldn't be far on the other side of the mine entrance a few feet from here.  Return after he has it for a bit coin to line your pockets!
Ah, he has it, then?  Maybe he'll actually get some work done, now.  Here you go, then - as promised.  *hands over a sack of coins*
Work, work, work!  Sorry, can't talk now!
You didn't deliver that pick yet?

value.0:
The great Charnag Mine here in the Middledark fills the great central Shaft with industrial sounds and guttural shouts that echo once off the walls before descending into a fleeting and faraway bass. The cave walls glisten in any form of light, revealing the cold and cloying dampness that breeds small patches of mushrooms and large swaths of lichen. The fungus grows over several small cave openings lining the Shaft, suggesting tunnels and mines that extend perhaps even further than the Shaft is deep. 

The air within the Shaft moves imperceptibly, and sometimes if the moisture is high enough, those familiar with the surface may have the feeling that it is raining within the Shaft. Once on solid rock, though, the air is heavy and makes breathing laborious to those unfamiliar to it. A panoply of alien smells, the breath of fungus and the geothermal flatulence of the mine with small notes of something acidic, unsettle the Upperdark nose. 

Far above, effulgent worms dance about but are too far away to bring any comfort to those who desire warmth and light. Below, there is only the yawning black.
Something has dug up this mound of dirt. The ground around it is very soft, possibly stepping on to it may sink you below in to a hidden abcess.
